                       <h3>What is the Candidate Sourcing program and how does it differ from Mindfield’s previous Full-Cycle Recruitment offering?</h3>
                        <div>
                         <p>
                          The Candidate Sourcing program supports hiring managers by taking a simplified job order, hosting the job on a branded careers site and broadcasting it to a range of popular and effective job boards. 
                          The candidates will be visible to hiring managers as soon as they have completed the streamlined online application process.
                          Unlike with the previous Full Cycle Recruitment offering, Mindfield will not  be screening and scheduling interviews for these candidates.  
                         </p>
                        </div>
                    
                        <h3>What happened to my existing jobs opened prior to January of 2018?</h3>
                        <div>
                         <p>
                          Any Full Cycle Recruitment jobs that were still open as of January 2nd, 2018 will be closed and re-opened as Candidate Sourcing jobs. 
                          All Full Cycle Recruitment jobs that had outstanding candidates will be viewable in the HirePortal until all candidates are updated. 
                          <br/><br/>
                          Any new job opened as of January 2nd will be opened as a Candidate Sourcing job.  
                         </p>
                        </div>
                    
                        <h3>Why do I need to mark candidates as Hired?</h3>
                        <div>
                         <p>
                          If you don’t mark a candidate as Hired, we may reach out this candidate in email campaigns regarding new job opportunities.
                          This can be confusing and disruptive for the candidate, and can be easily avoided by telling us who you have hired.
                          This will also let us know how effective our sourcing efforts have been. 
                         </p>
                        </div>
                        
                        <h3>Do I need to mark the Candidates as Hired in Peoplesoft?</h3>
                        <div>
                         <p>
                          As of January 2nd, 2018, all candidate who applied through a candidate sourcing job will no longer automatically sync to PeopleSoft for hiring.
                          Hiring Managers will be responsible for entering all new hire information into PeopleSoft in addition to updating the candidate to Hired in the Mindfield HirePortal. 
                         </p>
                        </div>
                        
                        <h3>What is a duplicate job check?</h3>
                        <div>
                         <p>
                          Most job boards have quality controls in place to prevent spamming. 
                          When an organization posts the same job title as another active job already posted at a given location it may get flagged as spam and can lead to suspension from that job board.
                          Therefore, Mindfield has put a duplicate job check in place to prevent this.    
                         </p>
                        </div>
                        
                        <h3>How do I request additional sourcing actions?</h3>
